# Schema must always be in sync

`database/schema.sql` is the canonical, idempotent source of truth for the
Supabase database. **It must reflect the live schema at all times.**

## When this rule fires

Any change that affects the database — even one column — including:

- Creating / editing a `*.sql` file in `database/`
- Adding or modifying a Supabase table, view, function, RPC, trigger, enum, RLS
  policy, index, constraint, comment, default, FK
- Hand-running SQL in the Supabase SQL editor that the user mentions
- Adding a new TypeScript field that maps to a new DB column

## What to do

After writing the migration file (e.g. `database/foo.sql`), **always also
update `database/schema.sql`** in the same edit batch:

1. Locate the matching `-- SECTION N: ...` block (tables go near related
   tables, indexes go in `SECTION 23: INDEXES`, enums in `SECTION 1: ENUM
   TYPES`, functions/views go at the end of their parent section).
2. Add the new object using **idempotent** syntax so re-running schema.sql is
   safe:
   - `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS …`
   - `ALTER TABLE … ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS …`
   - `CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS …`
   - `CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION …` / `CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW …`
   - `DO $$ BEGIN CREATE TYPE … EXCEPTION WHEN duplicate_object THEN NULL; END $$;`
3. Mirror any RLS / GRANT statements introduced by the migration.
4. Keep section headers and ordering — schema.sql is read top-to-bottom as a
   bootstrap script.

## Do NOT

- Do **not** delete the per-feature migration file in `database/` after folding
  it in. The migration files are still used for live deployments; schema.sql is
  the consolidated picture.
- Do **not** introduce non-idempotent statements into schema.sql.
- Do **not** leave the migration file and schema.sql out of sync. If you can't
  fold the change in, flag it explicitly to the user.

## Quick checklist before finishing

- [ ] Migration file written under `database/`
- [ ] Same change reflected in `database/schema.sql` in the matching section
- [ ] All new statements are idempotent
- [ ] RLS / GRANT / triggers updated where relevant
